This paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for Intrusion Detection Systems (IDSs) for network data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses adversarial machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes new explainability techniques for sequential data, which could also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
